Generally, the differential co-expression analysis is to see if or not the expression correlation of a gene-pair (e.g. two genes or molecules) changes between control and case samples22,47. Thus, the Pearson correlation coefficient (PCC) between genes i and j in control or case samples can be calculated as:4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
